<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc2f4efc5-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1712B"><num value="1712B">§ 1712B.</num><heading> Counseling for former prisoners of war</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may establish a program under which, upon the request of a veteran who is a former prisoner of war, the Secretary, within the limits of Department facilities, furnishes counseling to such veteran to assist such veteran in overcoming the psychological effects of the veteran’s detention or internment as a prisoner of war.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc2f4efc6-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/99/166/tI/s107/a">Pub. L. 99–166, title I, § 107(a)</ref>, <date date="1985-12-03">Dec. 3, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/945">99 Stat. 945</ref>, § 612B; renumbered § 1712B and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/83">Pub. L. 102–83</ref>, §§ 4(a)(3), (4), (b)(1), (2)(E), 5(a), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404-406">105 Stat. 404–406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
